---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Vote" description="Campaign and manifesto page.">
  <section class="vote-page">
    <section class="pillars">
      <h1><span class="lead-word">Better</span><span class="main-word">Portfolios</span></h1>
      <h1><span class="lead-word">Stronger</span><span class="main-word">Networks</span></h1>
      <h1><span class="lead-word">More</span><span class="main-word">Internships</span></h1>
    </section>

    <section class="candidates">
      <article class="candidate">
        <div class="portrait">
          <img class="portrait-image" src="/images/sebastian-chair.jpg" alt="Sebastian portrait" />
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-heading">
          <h2>MSSA Chair</h2>
          <p class="candidate-name">Sebastian</p>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-copy manifesto-copy">
          <p>
            Through being leader of MSSA Climate Action Group, as well as creative
            director of MSSA photography, I am confident that I can benefit the role
            of MSSA Chair in every scale, for the individual student, for our community,
            and for how we present ourselves and collaborate with the world beyond the school.
            If you have met me, you know I am outgoing and friendly; always happy to talk
            and help you. As chair, some of my current goals are to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Involve the architecture staff / professors within MSSA subgroups through architecture competitions with students and teachers in teams.</li>
            <li>Give the ability for connectivity through a more rigorous interactive online website.</li>
            <li>Collaborate with cross faculties from both Universities MMU and UoM for inter curricular events specifically with the visual arts faculty and civil engineering faculty.</li>
            <li>Clear information and liaison between what students actually want vs what they are offered in the MSSA.</li>
            <li>Societies made accessible through defined calendars and schedules for friendly tournaments for the sports and clear events and incentives for the students.</li>
            <li>Quantitative outputs that result in verifiable and CV transferable experiences from MSSA to boost student employability.</li>
            <li>Direct relation with companies to boost and fast track active participants of the MSSA for summer or easter architecture internships.</li>
            <li>Greater reach for architecture companies, guest speakers and industry opportunities, for real networking.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Vote for Sebastian for MSSA to experience, grow and perform.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="candidate">
        <div class="portrait">
          <img
            class="portrait-image portrait-image--secretary"
            src="/images/ansh-secretary-V2.JPG"
            alt="Ansh portrait"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-heading">
          <h2>MSSA Secretary</h2>
          <p class="candidate-name">Ansh</p>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-copy manifesto-copy">
          <p>
            Hi, I'm Ansh (Ash), currently in BA2 and the Co-Lead of EDI Fora this year.
            Through this role, I've had the opportunity to work closely with students
            across different backgrounds, year groups, and interests, helping foster a
            more inclusive and engaging student environment. I am now looking to take
            this further by running for MSSA General Secretary / Inclusions Officer,
            where I can apply my experience on a wider scale.
          </p>
          <p>
            As an active member of MSA, I've seen how strong MSSA is as a platform for
            connection. Building on the momentum created by the previous committee, I
            want to help it grow into a space where every student feels welcomed,
            represented, and encouraged to take part.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Create a more connected and supportive student community across all year groups.</li>
            <li>Introduce peer-to-peer support networks linking different years for guidance and advice.</li>
            <li>Advocate for student-staff-industry interaction to build wider networks.</li>
            <li>Encourage collaborative events across societies, including those outside MSSA, and across subgroups to break social silos.</li>
            <li>Organise low-pressure, informal social spaces that encourage genuine interaction and participation.</li>
            <li>Support a wider variety of events that reflect different cultures, interests, and backgrounds.</li>
            <li>Ensure inclusion is considered in how events are planned, promoted, and experienced.</li>
            <li>Facilitate student-staff-industry interactions to support portfolio development, research opportunities, and mentorship.</li>
            <li>Expand engagement with alumni and professionals through talks, networking sessions, and meetups.</li>
            <li>Support external studio visits and workshops.</li>
            <li>Improve communications so more people are aware of events and opportunities.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            With past experience as Co-Lead for EDI Fora and Events Co-ordinator for
            MSSA iDesign, I have been actively involved in organising events, curating
            student design competitions, collaborating across groups, and contributing
            to initiatives that bring students together beyond academics.
          </p>
          <p>
            I am approachable, proactive, and committed to representing student voices
            responsibly. I want to help create an MSSA that works for everyone, not
            just a few. I am committed to helping MSSA become more connected,
            inclusive, and student-focused. With your support, I will work to ensure
            that every student feels they have a place within this community.
          </p>
          <p>Help build an inclusive and more connected MSSA.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="shared-manifesto">
      <p class="shared-label">Shared Manifesto</p>
      <div class="shared-copy shared-copy-block manifesto-copy">
        <p>
          Together, we want MSSA to be more connected and more ambitious in what it
          offers students. Our aim is to strengthen the sense of community within MSA
          while also expanding the opportunities, networks, and collaborations available
          through student life.
        </p>
        <p>
          We believe MSSA should not only bring people together socially, but also act
          as a stronger platform for participation, visibility, and growth. Connecting
          students across year groups, disciplines, and backgrounds, while opening
          clearer pathways to creative collaboration, industry engagement, and wider
          opportunity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our shared vision is for an MSSA that feels welcoming and representative, but
          also active, outward-looking, and genuinely valuable: a society that helps
          students connect, contribute, and grow both within the school and beyond it.
        </p>
        <p>Vote Sebastian &amp; Ash for a more connected and ambitious MSSA.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .vote-page {
    --manifesto-copy-size: clamp(13.125rem, 23.625vw, 16.40625rem);
    --shared-manifesto-copy-size: calc(var(--manifesto-copy-size) * 1.1);
    --divider-space: 5.15625rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--divider-space);
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 64rem;
    padding: 5rem 0;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pillars h1 {
    align-items: baseline;
    color: var(--ink);
    display: flex;
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    gap: 0.22em;
    justify-content: center;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .lead-word {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    font-size: calc(20pt - 5pt);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .main-word {
    font-size: 20pt;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .candidates {
    align-items: start;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.12);
    display: grid;
    gap: 3rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    padding-top: var(--divider-space);
  }

  .candidate {
    --profile-size: clamp(10rem, 18vw, 12.5rem);
    align-content: start;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    justify-items: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .candidate-heading {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    justify-items: center;
  }

  .portrait {
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    background: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.14);
    border-radius: 50%;
    overflow: hidden;
    width: var(--profile-size);
  }

  .portrait-image {
    display: block;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 38%;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .portrait-image--secretary {
    object-position: center 54%;
    transform: scale(1.08);
    transform-origin: center 54%;
  }

  .candidate h2 {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.1vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .candidate-name {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .candidate-copy,
  .shared-copy {
    color: rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.78);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11.25pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .candidate-copy {
    width: var(--manifesto-copy-size);
  }

  .candidate-copy p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .manifesto-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .manifesto-copy ul {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.15rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .manifesto-copy li {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .shared-copy {
    width: var(--shared-manifesto-copy-size);
  }

  .shared-copy-block {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .shared-copy-block p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .shared-manifesto {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(27, 55, 67, 0.12);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-items: center;
    padding-top: var(--divider-space);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .shared-label {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.1vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: left;
    width: var(--manifesto-copy-size);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .vote-page {
      gap: 4.5rem;
      padding: 4rem 0;
    }

    .pillars {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .candidates {
      gap: 3.5rem;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
